04, Elon Musk led Tesla\'s first funding round and became the company\'s chairman, subsequently claiming to be a co-founder; in 2008, he was named chief executive officer. The company began production of its first car model, the Roadster sports car, in 2008; the Model S sedan in 2012; the Model X SUV in 2015; the Model 3 sedan in 2017; the Model Y crossover in 2020; the Tesla Semi truck in 2022; and the Cybertruck pickup truck in 2023.\nTesla is one of the world\'s most valuable companies in terms of market capitalization. Starting in July 2020, it has been the world\'s most valuable automaker. From October 2021 to March 2022, Tesla was a US$1 trillion company, the sixth US company to reach that valuation. In 2023, the company was ranked 69th in the Forbes Global 2000. In 2024, the company led the battery electric vehicle market, with 17.6% share.\nTesla exceeded $1 trillion in market capitalization again between November 2024 and February 2025, and since May 2025. In November 2025, Tesla approved a pay package worth $1 trillion for Musk, which he is to receive over 10 years if he meets specific goals. By the end of  2025, the company lost its status as world\'s leading manufacturer of electric vehicles.\nTesla has been the subject of lawsuits, boycotts, government scrutiny, and journalistic criticism, stemming from allegations of multiple cases of whistleblower retaliation, worker rights violations such as sexual harassment and anti-union activities, safety defects leading to dozens of recalls, the lack of a public relations department, and controversial statements from Musk, including overpromising on the company\'s driving assist technology and product release timelines.\n\nPage: History of Tesla, Inc.\nSummary: Tesla, Inc. is an electric vehicle manufacturer and clean energy company founded in San Carlos, California in 2003 by American entrepreneurs Martin Eberhard and Marc Tarpenning. The company is named after Serbian-American inventor Nikola Tesla. Tesla is the world\'s leading electric vehicle manufacturer by market cap. As of 2023, Tesla\'s global vehicle sales were 1.77 million units annually, the 14th-highest total among auto manufacturers worldwide.\n\n\n\nPage: Criticism of Tesla, Inc.\nSummary: Tesla, Inc. has been criticized for its cars, workplace culture, business practices, and occupational safety. Many of the criticisms are also directed toward Elon Musk, the company\'s CEO and Product Architect. Critics have also accused Tesla of deceptive marketing, unfulfilled promises, and fraud. The company is currently facing criminal and civil investigations into its self-driving claims. Critics have highlighted Tesla\'s downplaying of issues, and Tesla\'s alleged retaliation against several whistleblowers.\nThe safety and quality of Tesla cars and services have been questioned. There have been hundreds of reports of sudden unintended acceleration, brake failures, and "whompy wheels" – collapsing wheels due to faulty car suspension. These safety and quality problems have been compounded in the past by the poor wait times of Tesla\'s customer service. Some features such as Autopilot, Full Self-Driving beta, and Passenger Play (a feature allowing riders to play Tesla games while in motion) have been criticized for their careless deployment. Critics have noted that some Tesla cars have had poor build quality due to rushed testing, leading to a high ratio of flawed vehicles. Others criticize the company', name='wikipedia', tool_call_id='call_46JSiOqHaeLuDM7ZRbsiRkaa'), AIMessage(content='', additional_kwargs={'tool_calls': [{'id': 'call_7SUKCQBYoB7l4ZlDv90U8Pot', 'function': {'arguments': '{"search_query":"Tesla, Inc."}', 'name': 'WikipediaSummaryValidator', 'parameters': None}, 'type': 'function'}], 'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 21, 'prompt_tokens': 1045, 'total_tokens': 1066, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': 0, 'audio_tokens': 0, 'reasoning_tokens': 0, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': 0}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': 0, 'cached_tokens': 0}, 'input_tokens': 0, 'output_tokens': 0, 'input_tokens_details': None}, 'model_name': 'gpt-4o-mini', 'system_fingerprint': 'fp_eb37e061ec', 'finish_reason': 'tool_calls', 'logprobs': None}, id='run-d10435e4-840d-4c0b-a804-836816c697f4-0', tool_calls=[{'name': 'WikipediaSummaryValidator', 'args': {'search_query': 'Tesla, Inc.'}, 'id': 'call_7SUKCQBYoB7l4ZlDv90U8Pot', 'type': 'tool_call'}], usage_metadata={'input_tokens': 1045, 'output_tokens': 21, 'total_tokens': 1066, 'input_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'cache_read': 0}, 'output_token_details': {'audio': 0, 'reasoning': 0}}), ToolMessage(content='Done.', name='WikipediaSummaryValidator', tool_call_id='call_7SUKCQBYoB7l4ZlDv90U8Pot'), AIMessage(content="Tesla, Inc. is an American multinational automotive and clean energy company founded in July 2003 by Martin Eberhard and Marc Tarpenning, originally named Tesla Motors. The company is named after the inventor Nikola Tesla and is headquartered in Austin, Texas. Here are some key milestones and achievements in Tesla's history:\n\n1. **Founding (2003)**: Tesla was established to accelerate the world's transition to sustainable energy. The founders aimed to create electric vehicles (EVs) that could compete with traditional gasoline-powered cars.\n\n2. **Elon Musk's Involvement (2004)**: Elon Musk led Tesla's first funding round in February 2004 and became the chairman of the board. He later claimed to be a co-founder, and in 2008, he was appointed as the CEO.\n\n3. **First Production Car - Roadster (2008)**: Tesla began production of its first car, the Roadster, which was the first highway-legal electric vehicle to use lithium-ion battery cells. It showcased the potential of electric vehicles and helped establish Tesla's reputation.\n\n4. **Model S Launch (2012)**: The Model S, a luxury all-electric sedan, was launched and received critical acclaim for its performance, safety, and range. It significantly boosted Tesla's visibility and sales.\n\n5. **Expansion of Product Line**:\n   - **Model X (2015)**: An all-electric SUV with distinctive falcon-wing doors.\n   - **Model 3 (2017)**: A more affordable sedan aimed at mass-market consumers, which became one of the best-selling electric cars globally.\n   - **Model Y (2020)**: A compact SUV that further expanded Tesla's market reach.\n   - **Tesla Semi (2022)**: An all-electric truck aimed at the freight industry.\n   - **Cybertruck (2023)**: A futuristic electric pickup truck that garnered significant attention.\n\n6. **Market Leadership**: Tesla became the world's most valuable automaker by market capitalization starting in July 2020. It reached a valuation of $1 trillion in October 2021, becoming the sixth U.S. company to achieve this milestone.\n\n7. **Global Sales**: By 2023, Tesla's annual global vehicle sales reached approximately 1.77 million units, making it the leading electric vehicle manufacturer by market cap.\n\n8. **Challenges and Criticism**: Tesla has faced various challenges, including lawsuits, government scrutiny, and criticism regarding workplace culture, safety issues, and the handling of self-driving technology claims.\n\nTesla continues to innovate in the electric vehicle and clean energy sectors, maintaining a significant share of the battery electric vehicle market.", additional_kwargs={'refusal': None}, response_metadata={'token_usage': {'completion_tokens': 542, 'prompt_tokens': 1076, 'total_tokens': 1618, 'completion_tokens_details': {'accepted_prediction_tokens': 0, 'audio_tokens': 0, 'reasoning_tokens': 0, 'rejected_prediction_tokens': 0}, 'prompt_tokens_details': {'audio_tokens': 0, 'cached_tokens': 1024}, 'input_tokens': 0, 'output_tokens': 0, 'input_tokens_details': None}, 'model_name': 'gpt-4o-mini', 'system_fingerprint': 'fp_eb37e061ec', 'finish_reason': 'stop', 'logprobs': None}, id='run-69638ec5-b3c8-43a9-a433-22c483c59271-0', usage_metadata={'input